summary: Broadchurch a beautiful locale and gruesome crime
title: Broadchurch a beautiful locale and gruesome crime
body:
Broadchurch a beautiful locale and gruesome crime

A beautiful town of Broadchurch experiences one of the most horrific crimes that of death of a 10 year old boy Tom. The series in both intense and filled with tragedy. However, each character seems more and more interesting especially the DI Alec Hardy who is investigating the crime. Though physically unwell he is quite obsessed with the crime and does everything in his power to bring in as many people into the net as possible. As is with big social waves there are always innocent people who become scapegoats. The same happens with the characters involved.

The assistant DI is a woman Olivia Miller both set out to nab the killer. However, the killer is soon found in midst with them. It shakes the foundations of the family making them take paths that were not visible before. Public interest and pressure both are quite evident in the story line. People and press so not stop short of digging into the past of the DI himself. His past yielding some fodder to enable accusing him too.

Season 2 of this series is the Sanbrook murders where in Claire Ripley alleges she is in danger from her husband Lee Ashworth. Though she claims to have information about the murders she does not provide it to Hardy. Ellie senses something fishy which is soon vindicated when Claire ends up meeting Lee for sexual relations. Soon Hardy stops entertaining Claire’s claims of danger from her husband. Thereafter, the crime falls open and Hardy is able to find the killer. This season is edge of the seat entertainment because of dual suspense of ongoing Tom Latimer case and this crime series. Hardy has also overcome arrhythmia and now lives with his daughter.


Season 3 is when Ellie is raped by an unknown person when she visits her friend’s house for a birthday party. Her brain has blocked out the details, but her trust in herself and in Hardy ensures that the killer is brought to justice. Though the first two series are quite intriguing, the third one though visually brilliant fails to make the mark. Broadchurch all in all is an interesting crime series, quite a must watch for gripping acting and scenic locales.

title: David Tenant Added To C2E2 Lineup
body:
David Tenant Added To C2E2 Lineup

ReedPOP, the world’s leading producer of pop culture events, announced that David Tennant (Dr. Who, Marvel’s Jessica Jones) will be coming to C2E2 (Chicago Comic & Entertainment Expo) this year on March 23rd and 24th. Tennant will be participating in panels, autograph sessions and photo ops over his two-day span in the Windy City. Thought this news might be of interest to your readers!
